      Oversampling refers to various methods that aim to increase number of instances from the underrepresented class in the dataset. 
      Out of the various methods, Synthetic Minority Over-Sampling Technique (SMOTE) is used. 
      SMOTE’s main advantage is that by creating synthetic observations instead of reusing existing observations.

      # Test Model complexity
      neig = np.arange(1, 30)
      train_accuracy = []
      test_accuracy = []
      # Check different values of k  
      for i, k in enumerate(neig):
          # k from 1 to 30(exclude)
          knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
          # Fit with knn
          knn.fit(X_train,y_train)
          #train accuracy
          train_accuracy.append(knn.score(X_train, y_train))
          # test accuracy
          test_accuracy.append(knn.score(X_test, y_test))
      ​
      # Plot
      plt.figure(figsize=[13,8])
      plt.plot(neig, test_accuracy, label = 'Testing Accuracy')
      plt.plot(neig, train_accuracy, label = 'Training Accuracy')
      plt.legend()
      plt.title('k value VS Accuracy')
      plt.xlabel('Number of Neighbors')
      plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
      plt.xticks(neig)
      plt.show()
      print("Best accuracy is {} with K = {}".format(np.max(test_accuracy),1+test_accuracy.index(np.max(test_accuracy))))
      Best accuracy is 0.8064516129032258 with K = 24

      Four models are prepared to understand the best model:
          Model-1 - KNN Model without hyperparameter tuning and with imbalanced train data
          Model-2 - KNN Model with hyperparameter tuning and with imbalanced train data
          Model-3 - KNN Model without hyperparameter tuning and with balanced train data    
          Model-4 - KNN Model with hyperparameter tuning and with balanced train data
          
      When compared to imbalanced train data, Balanced train data helped to predict our objective (predict NOT normal conditions - Type_H and Type_S).
      From the above observation, Hypertuning is not helping in this case study. 
      Hence the "Model-3 - KNN Model without hyperparameter tuning and with balanced train data" will be the final model
       
      # Conclusion:

      Conclusion:¶

       
      Models          Recall Score for Class Type_H and Type_S (%)    f1-score for Class Type_H and Type_S (%)    Accuracy (%)
      ​
      Model-1                         71 and 88                                          73 and 89                    80.6

      Model-4                         65 and 90                                          61 and 91                    77.4   
      ​
      Our objective for us to predict NOT the normal conditions (Type_H and Type_S) compared to predict the normal conditions.
      Hence accuracy will not be helpful.
      Recall would help us for this case study.
      f1-score will be the harmonic mean of precision and recall
      From the observation, with respect to our objective, "Model-3 - KNN Model without hyperparameter tuning and with balanced train data" will be the final best model.
